The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The use of regularization techniques such as Tikhonov and Landweber suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG), while the iterative approach and hardware efficiency point towards numerical analysis (cs.NA). The signal processing aspect of the algorithm also suggests the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SP), and the use of real-world applications suggests the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SI).
